    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The science concerned with the use of radiation, such as X-rays and radioactive materials in the diagnosis and treatment of disease. For the application of techniques producing radiographic images, use "radiography."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046415/Concise Medical Dictionary (1998)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>La ciencia y práctica de tratar con rayos X o radiación nuclear. Para la aplicación de técnicas, que producen imágenes radiográficas, use "radiografía".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>De wetenschap die zich bezighoudt met het gebruik van straling, zoals röntgenstraling en radioactieve materialen voor de diagnose en behandeling van ziekte. Gebruik 'radiografie' voor de toepassing van technieken die radiografische beelden produceren.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
